 Reading Questions Answer Checker To check your answers put them in the appropriate box and click the &lsquo;Check&rsquo; button. Every checker box can do arithmetic and calculate standard functions (see calculator help). If you give decimal answers, give them to at least 3 decimal places.
As you work you should have pencil and paper handy for calculations and thinking!
Note: some questions ask for a formula. For the checker we ask you to plug a value into the formula. For your pset you still need to give the whole formula.
//DEBUG PARAMETERS //Because we don&rsquo;t show solutions for pset checkers we use //this to give a showanswer button during the debugging phase var debugans = undefined; //release //var debugans = kDebugAnswer; //debug problemNumber = 0; wl(&quot;&lt;h3&gt;Calculator&lt;/h3&gt;&quot;); writecalculator(&ldquo;psetcheckcalcid&rdquo;, &ldquo;Calculate&rdquo;); whr(kdivcol,kdivwid);
//Problem 1 problemNumber++; wl(problemheader(problemNumber)); var s; var partName, problemName, buttonLabel, answerArray, correct; s = emphtext(&ldquo;We suggest you use R to do the computations for this problem.&rdquo;); wl(s); wl(kp); s = &ldquo;Suppose we have the following table of counts for the outcomes 0-6.&rdquo;; wl(s); wl(kp); writetable([[&lsquo;Outcome&rsquo;, 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6], [&lsquo;Observed&rsquo;,&lsquo;5&rsquo;,&lsquo;11&rsquo;,&lsquo;13&rsquo;,&lsquo;7&rsquo;,&lsquo;2&rsquo;,&lsquo;1&rsquo;,&lsquo;1&rsquo;]], &ldquo;class=&lsquo;basicborder&rsquo;&rdquo;, &ldquo;class=&lsquo;basiccells&rsquo;&rdquo;, &ldquo;class=&lsquo;k&rsquo;&rdquo;, 2); wl(kp); s = &ldquo;We hypothesize that the data is drawn from a binomial(6, 0.4) distribution.&rdquo;; wl(s); wl(kp); s = &ldquo;(a) Compute the likelihood ratio statistic $G$.&rdquo;; wl(s); wl(kbr); partName = problemNumber + &quot; (a)&quot;; problemName = &ldquo;prob&rdquo; + partName; buttonLabel = &ldquo;Check problem &quot; + partName; writeNumericBox(partName+&ldquo;id&rdquo;, 11.89567, buttonLabel, 0.002, kuseCorrectVal); wl(kp); s = &ldquo;(b) Compute the Pearson chi square statistic $X^2$.&rdquo;; wl(s); wl(kbr); partName = problemNumber + &quot; (b)&rdquo;; problemName = &ldquo;prob&rdquo; + partName; buttonLabel = &ldquo;Check problem &quot; + partName; writeNumericBox(partName+&ldquo;id&rdquo;, 15.1242, buttonLabel, 0.002, kuseCorrectVal); wl(kp); s = &ldquo;(c) How many degrees of freedom are there in the chi square null distribution?&rdquo;; wl(s); wl(kbr); partName = problemNumber + &quot; (c)&rdquo;; problemName = &ldquo;prob&rdquo; + partName; buttonLabel = &ldquo;Check problem &quot; + partName; writeNumericBox(partName+&ldquo;id&rdquo;, 6, buttonLabel, 0.001, kuseCorrectVal); wl(kp); s = &ldquo;(d) Compute the $p$-value (based on the $G$-statistic).&rdquo;; wl(s); wl(kbr); partName = problemNumber + &quot; (d)&rdquo;; problemName = &ldquo;prob&rdquo; + partName; buttonLabel = &ldquo;Check problem &quot; + partName; writeNumericBox(partName+&ldquo;id&rdquo;, 0.064337, buttonLabel, 0.002, kuseCorrectVal); wl(kp); whr(kdivcol,kdivwid);
